'From Squeak 2.3 beta of Nov 25, 1998 on 7 January 1999 at 8:14:33 am'!"Change Set:		SafePassivateDate:			7 January 1999Author:			Dan IngallsFixes an obscure problem with SystemWindows...	If you dropped an active window into a book,	then turned to another page, then clicked on another window...	the window in the book would try to redisplay without a pointer to the world"!!SystemWindow methodsFor: 'top window' stamp: 'di 1/7/1999 08:14'!passivate	"Make me unable to respond to mouse and keyboard"	self setStripeColorsFrom: self paneColor.	self submorphsDo: [:m | m lock].	self world ifNotNil:		[self world displayWorld] "clean damage now, so dont merge this rect with new top window"! !